						<div class="postbody">I've been toying with recording some gameplay to an AVI recently and, no matter what I do the audio seems to get horribly out of sync. I was using the Xvid, MPEG 4 codec. I played with a bunch of the settings, but nothing seemed to help. Anyone have similar problems?
<br />
<br />I think if I'm really interested in recording video I may have to just train a camera on the television and hope there aren't scanline artifacts.  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif" alt=":D" title="Very Happy" /></div>

