				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">With FCEU derivatives, the reason this happens is because the frame rate is not exactly 60fps in NTSC, but the frame rate stored in the AVI is 60fps. However, the audio runs at the slightly different speed, causing skew. I used to use Avisynth to sync everything up, but I would surmise that tokumaru's method of using VDub would work as well (although I would test it with some quite long captures first, just to be on the safe side).</div>

